Assembly Bill 1056 requires community colleges to convert from a paper-based transcript process to an electronic system called eTranscripts. The legislature provided one-time funding to effect this transition.  The California Community Colleges Chancellorâs Office created a mini-grant program to disburse these funds to the colleges.
	 
In December 2012 EVC applied for three mini-grants of $5,000 each and completed the requirements of those grants by June 2013.  Implementation of eTranscripts has now been verified by California Community Colleges Technology Center and payment has been authorized in the amount of $15,000.  
	 
This electronic system to transmit and receive student transcripts gives EVC the ability to:
	 
send and receive electronic transcripts based on California Electronic Transcript standard;
import the California Electronic Transcript standard electronic transcript into our campus student information system;
respond to electronic requests and send the California Electronic Transcript Standard transcript.
